    - "S1: R1 acceptance grep is brittle — `grep -n 'stdout=subprocess.PIPE' | grep -E '_spawn_orchestrator|line 69[0-9]'` searches the post-filter output for literal '_spawn_orchestrator' or 'line 69x' which never appears in grep -n output, so the check always passes regardless of code state. Need a scoped check anchored to _spawn_orchestrator function body."
    - "S1: R2 acceptance + spec body — `model=<configured-or-detected>` is ambiguous on dispatch_start. The orchestrator subprocess hasn't run yet, so the actual model is unknown until the envelope arrives. Spec must define what model field carries on dispatch_start (omit/sentinel/config-read) vs. dispatch_complete (envelope-extracted)."
    - "S1: R7 acceptance is vague — `or the orphan-start path documented behavior holds` is unverifiable. metrics.py emits no warning for orphan dispatch_start (warns only for dispatch_complete and dispatch_error); the test should assert pair_dispatch_events returns exactly one paired record (R2) with zero logger warnings."
